id: pm-u8n5
title: "Search relevance eval harness: implement nDCG/MRR runner and gate in CI"
description: "pm-22x2 and pm-fhsg (golden-query eval harness) are closed but the harness was filed as a task/story, not necessarily shipped as a CI gate. There is no actual nDCG/MRR runner in src/core/search/ and no CI job measuring search quality regressions. This means relevance regressions from corpus changes, hybrid weight changes, or provider upgrades go undetected."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:search",ci,eval,quality,relevance
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:03:46.324Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-20T06:22:56.098Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- `pm eval` command or `pm reindex --eval` subcommand runs golden-query set against current index\n- Outputs nDCG@10, MRR@10 per query and aggregate\n- Golden queries stored in `.agents/pm/search/eval-queries.json` (gittracked, human-curated)\n- CI gate fails if nDCG drops below baseline by more than epsilon\n- Supports both keyword and hybrid modes"
parent: pm-ydp6
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: Search relevance eval harness (pm eval) shipped with nDCG/MRR runner + CI gate.
